From 6bc71f037fc57298a663b95ac7532356d078696a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joshua-Eisenhart <40147598+Joshua-Eisenhart@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 21:21:01 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] fix(eval): harden cr_cross_engine_parity sensor to verify
 real sim-eval content_address
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Audit found the sensor only checked the content_address PREFIX, while a
real @lev-os/sim-eval provider computes an FNV-1a-32 hash and rejects
mismatches — so the sensor was more permissive than the real validator
on exactly the field a provider computes (a false-green hole). The
sensor now recomputes the FNV-1a-32 content_address from the record and
blocks on mismatch (content_address_mismatch), matching the real
producer; verified it reproduces the real value sim-eval:fnv1a32:1840d25c.

Fixtures regenerated with real content addresses (were hand-authored
placeholders). New bad-address case: a record well-formed in every field
except a wrong content_address must block. Load-bearing by mutation test
(independent audit): neutralizing the hash check flips bad-address from
block to pass, so the gate is what blocks it, not an incidental check.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
